# Goal

Integrate the Vineyard Quality Map (Phase 5) into the dashboard. `maps.js` (473 lines) is fully implemented but completely orphaned — no DOM, no CONFIG, no nav entry, no script tag. Wire it up end-to-end so users can view color-coded vineyard section heatmaps by metric.

# Constraints

- Vanilla JS only — no npm packages or frameworks
- Spanish labels only — "Mapa" for the nav tab
- Mobile responsive before considered complete
- CDN-only dependencies (Chart.js 4.4.1, SheetJS 0.18.5)
- File responsibilities: CONFIG additions → `config.js`, DOM → `index.html`, routing → `app.js`
- Do not restructure or refactor existing views

# Files likely involved

| File | Action |
|---|---|
| `js/config.js` | Add `fieldLotToSection`, `fieldLotRanchPatterns`, `mapMetrics`, `vineyardSections` |
| `index.html` | Add `<option value="map">Mapa</option>`, `#view-map` panel with DOM elements maps.js expects, `<script src="js/maps.js">` |
| `js/app.js` | Add `case 'map':` to `refresh()` switch, handle filter visibility for map view |
| `css/styles.css` | Map panel layout, SVG container sizing, section detail panel, mobile responsive rules |
| `js/maps.js` | Bug fixes only if integration reveals issues — do NOT rewrite |

# Acceptance criteria

1. "Mapa" appears as 6th option in `#nav-select` dropdown
2. Clicking "Mapa" shows the SVG vineyard map with sections color-coded by default metric (Brix)
3. Metric selector switches between Brix, pH, tANT, TA — map recolors
4. Clicking a section opens the detail panel with per-section KPIs and lot breakdown
5. Ranch selector switches between VDG (Monte Xanic), VON (Kompali), and other ranches
6. Color scale legend renders below the map
7. Layout is responsive — single column on mobile, side panel on desktop
8. No console errors on load or interaction
